@rprouse We already do that. There is a hard-coded string that is used if no attribute is found. It's a little silly, but we have been doing it that way for many years. We do the same thing in NUnit and NUnitLite, so I might pull it out to a common class somewhere.

@oznetmaster Of course, we can't change what's already out there. :-)

Additionally, I don't think we can change how we version assemblies for 3.0 because the number we used (like 200) would be lower than the numbers that have been generated automatically for the alphas, betas and first rc. We could change how we do it for 3.1 and higher versions though.
